### getSize() {#a3a8d45f58be1922403c4d098c8c65eeb}

<MemberDefinition
  template={<>template &lt;class ELFT&gt;</>}
  prototype={<>size&#95;t llvm::object::Elf&#95;Nhdr&#95;Impl&lt; ELFT &gt;::getSize (size&#95;t Align) const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Get the size of the note, including name, descriptor, and padding.

Both the start and the end of the descriptor are aligned by the section alignment. In practice many 64-bit systems deviate from the generic ABI by using sh&#95;addralign=4.
